  "description": "Herbert Gustaf Ragnar Eliasson was a high school teacher and prominent member of various educational and sports organizations in Sweden. He was born on June 6, 1902 in Varberg to director August E. and Mathilda Dahlgren. He married Lisa Cedarbom in 1937 and had two children, Eva and Inger. Eliasson obtained a Master of Philosophy degree from Lund University in 1929 and an engineering degree from Chalmers University of Technology in 1924. He held teaching positions at various schools and was appointed as an assistant teacher in Oskarshamn in 1940. Eliasson served as acting principal in Trollhattan from 1932 to 1938 and in Oskarshamn from 1941 to 1945. He also held various leadership positions including chairman of the Gothenburg district of the Association of Part-time Teachers from 1936 to 1939, chairman of the Youth Council in Oskarshamn since 1942, chairman of the Oskarshamn Sports Alliance since 1946, and chairman of the Oskarshamn Sports Hall Association since 1944. Eliasson's hobby was tennis."
